      "writtenOn": "2018-05-25T13:42:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "we are recompiling regexes in each iteration. Let\u0027s just accumulate a slice of regexes in this loop and after the loop compile regex once. It would be less code too",
      "revId": "f4f82c4640593ef4c05b174459f3e46a60fb7a58",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d1d7e2b2_e589ea2a",
        "filename": "scheduler/appengine/task/gitiles/gitiles.go",
        "patchSetId": 17
      },
      "lineNbr": 501,
      "author": {
        "id": 1153089
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-26T19:45:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "IMHO it\u0027s not worth it as this will make code harder-to-read and make little improvements to the speed (we hardly ever have more than one ref specification). In particular we may be adding regexes to different namespaces in the loop and would require an extra map from namespaces to the list of regexp strings (or an extra field in the watchedRefNamespace struct) to collect regexps and another loop over namespaces it the end of this function to have them compiled, i.e.\n\n  accumulatedRegexps :\u003d make(map[string]string)\n  for _, ref :\u003d range refsConfig {\n    ...\n    if _, exists :\u003d accumulatedRegexps[ns]; !exists {\n      accumulatedRegexps[ns] \u003d \"(\" + rs\n    } else {\n      accumulatedRegexps[ns] +\u003d \")|(\" + rs\n    }\n    ...\n  }\n\n  for ns, rs :\u003d range accumulatedRegexps {\n    w.namespaces[ns].addRegexp(rs + \")\")\n  }",
      "parentUuid": "c34d1500_25eb9e52",
      "revId": "f4f82c4640593ef4c05b174459f3e46a60fb7a58",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "45b083c2_d0a717f3",
        "filename": "scheduler/appengine/task/gitiles/gitiles.go",
        "patchSetId": 17
      },
      "lineNbr": 501,
      "author": {
        "id": 1114299
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-26T23:41:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i understand that you want to keep this function simple and I agree with that. I think there is a way to make it simple and efficient (linear, not square) at the same time:\n\n  regexps :\u003d map[string][]string{}\n  for _, ref :\u003d range refsConfig {\n    ...\n    regexps[ns] \u003d append(regexps[ns], rs)\n    ...\n  }\n\n  for ns, rs :\u003d range accumulatedRegexps {\n    w.namespaces[ns].childRegexp, _ \u003d re.Compile(\"(\" + strings.Join(\")|(\", rs) + \"(\")\n  }\n\nthe joining of regexps with OR can be extracted to a separate function if this looks too complicated here.\n\nNote that then you don\u0027t need addRegexp. Another problem with addRegexp that I have is that nobody except init would call it, so it has less reasons to be a separate function. A function that joins regexps with OR is more general, more likely to be reused, so to me it is more reasonable to have it.",
      "parentUuid": "d1d7e2b2_e589ea2a",
      "revId": "f4f82c4640593ef4c05b174459f3e46a60fb7a58",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
